Schering-Plough Corp said ChairmanRobert P. Luciano intends to recommend to the board at its nextregular meeting on October 27 that the quarterly dividend beincreased five cts, or 20 pct, to 30 cts a share effective withthe payment to be made in November.    The company also said it also plans to resume immediatelyits share repurchase plan and expects to buy about 200 mln dlrsof stock.     The company suspended the share repurchase programseptember 22  while it studied the proposed dividend increase,Schering said.    Schering-Plough had, under the plan announced June 23, beenauthorized to repurchase of 4.6 mln shares, a spokesman said.He was unable to say how many shares were repurchased prior tosuspension of the program.    The company said it expects continuing operations togenerate strong gains for rest of year and on into l988.     Itsaid Luciano will ask board to review dividend policy onceagain early next year. The dividend was previously increased inMay 1987 and February 1986. Reuter&#3;